replies.body:
I'm sure you mean bruisers {{champion:122}} {{champion:86}} {{champion:420}} 

Mobile damage dealers, that thrive on snowballing, are doing just as well on 3v3 as they are. Yasuo and Graves are two of the strongest DPS champs on the map. In contrast, most tanks aren't actually doing that well. Poppy, Sej, and Galio are doing well, while others have varying degrees of success. There are so many champs/comps that are potentially overbearing on TT that I don't feel like a draft mode would really help. 

Playing against premades is the real problem imo, especially on NA. On a map with no vision, or space to work with, even the slightest advantage in communication makes a large difference. Often it just leads to one-sided stomps, with the losing side being tilted while having no clue what to do.
